{"parentUuid":"be01f701-02c8-4282-bd0a-000423750e02","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"a6199312c888fb590","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012ZHZ1jgWnxandrkax3g9Vt","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→name: Ecosystem Wiring Audit\n     3→description: Deep audit of all inter-system signal pathways, what's alive vs dead vs dormant across dharma_swarm, trishula, AGNI, JK loops. Updated 2026-03-13.\n     4→type: project\n     5→---\n     6→\n     7→## Ecosystem Status (2026-03-13)\n     8→\n     9→### ALIVE\n    10→- **dharma_swarm daemon** (PID 70429): Python 3.14, SwarmManager, 120s interval, thread rotation works (mech=69, phenom=7)\n    11→  - BUT: can't spawn `claude -p` from within Claude Code (nested session error) — most features dormant\n    12→  - 13 cron jobs in cron_jobs.json — NONE execute (daemon doesn't parse cron_jobs.json)\n    13→- **Stigmergy**: 8,578 marks in `~/.dharma/stigmergy/marks.jsonl` (2.4MB), actively written\n    14→- **Witness logs**: `~/.dharma/witness/witness_YYYYMMDD.jsonl` — active but saturated with test data (170K+ gate validation entries)\n    15→- **SSH**: Both VPSes reachable (AGNI 157.245.193.15, RUSHABDEV 167.172.95.184)\n    16→- **CHAIWALA**: `~/.chaiwala/messages.db` (19MB) — daemon running but no consumers\n    17→\n    18→### FIXED (this session)\n    19→- **Trishula router**: Was stuck in 8,548-iteration loop on corrupted Feb 20 JSON. Quarantined to `~/trishula/quarantine/`\n    20→- **Nervous system v2**: Rewrote from monolithic claude -p to bash health check + triage + targeted dispatch\n    21→\n    22→### DEAD\n    23→- **Trishula syncs**: All rsync jobs stopped (agni_pull, agni_push, rush_pull, rush_push)\n    24→- **AGNI agent**: Silent 11 days (WORKING.md last modified Mar 2)\n    25→- **RUSHABDEV agent**: Silent 22 days (last heartbeat Feb 20, corrupted)\n    26→- **Local agent (DHARMIC_CLAWD)**: 1,621 spawn failures — missing `openclaw` binary in PATH\n    27→- **signal_map.json**: Code exists in signal_map.py, never initialized\n    28→\n    29→### DORMANT (code exists, not wired)\n    30→- Darwin Engine (evolution.py) — complete, never called from pulse\n    31→- Task dispatch (orchestrator.py) — complete, bypassed by pulse.py\n    32→- Agent pool (SwarmManager.spawn()) — never called, agents list stays empty\n    33→- Cron job execution — 13 jobs defined, no APScheduler integration\n    34→- Feedback loop — observations written but next pulse doesn't read prior results\n    35→\n    36→### Signal Flow\n    37→```\n    38→Agent execution → witness.jsonl + marks.jsonl (append-only JSONL)\n    39→                           ↓ (NOT YET WIRED)\n    40→               signal_map.json (aggregate confidence)\n    41→                           ↓ (NOT YET WIRED)\n    42→               context.py → agent briefing / attention routing\n    43→```\n    44→\n    45→JK autonomous loop: `nervous_system.sh` (launchd every 4h) → reads .loops/ state → dispatches focused claude -p\n    46→dharma_swarm: `swarm.run(120s)` → thread rotation → attempt pulse → blocked by nested error\n    47→\n    48→### Key State Files\n    49→- `~/.dharma/mission.json` — JK mission, status \"delegated\", stale since Mar 12\n    50→- `~/.dharma/thread_state.json` — thread rotation state (69 mechanistic, 7 phenomenological)\n    51→- `~/.dharma/living_state.json` — dream density (8486), last shakti Mar 11\n    52→- `~/jagat_kalyan/.loops/compounding_state.json` — audit progress, test counts\n    53→- `~/jagat_kalyan/.loops/attention_queue.json` — 3 BLOCKING + 4 NEEDS_EYES\n    54→- `~/jagat_kalyan/.loops/nervous_system_state.json` — nervous system dispatch log\n    55→- `~/.dharma/shared/jk_pulse.md` — pulse signal for morning brief pickup\n    56→\n    57→### 20 launchd agents loaded, 1 not loaded:\n    58→- `com.jagat-kalyan.heartbeat` — NOT LOADED (needs `launchctl load`)\n    59→- 14 others running (bridge-watcher PID 929 active, rest PID 0 = waiting)\n    60→- `com.claude-max-api` — error state (PID -78)\n    61→"}]},"uuid":"990d22ac-864d-45f7-a3ab-155e8570aed0","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:17:54.588Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"be01f701-02c8-4282-bd0a-000423750e02","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
