{"parentUuid":"91a9e5b2-e119-43b9-9f31-0cc0f63ce4ac","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"a6199312c888fb590","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018GwDLYAZJtJY4NRunB2fto","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# dharma_swarm — THE Runtime (Updated 2026-03-13)\n     2→\n     3→- **Location**: `~/dharma_swarm/` — 90+ Python files (65 top-level + engine/ subpackage + tui/ package), **2327 tests passing** (as of 2026-03-13)\n     4→- **What it is**: Working async multi-provider agent orchestrator with real LLM calls — **AUTONOMOUSLY RUNNING**\n     5→- **DAEMON CONFIRMED ALIVE (2026-03-13)**: PID in `~/.dharma/daemon.pid`, dispatching tasks every 120s via OpenRouter\n     6→  - 296 shared note files (4.3M), 8,481 stigmergy marks, agents completing tasks + writing notes\n     7→  - Agents: archeologist, architect, researcher — all making successful OpenRouter API calls\n     8→  - Living layers: dreams triggering, shakti perceptions generating, stigmergy marks accumulating\n     9→- **MULTI-PROVIDER FLEET (Updated 2026-03-13)**:\n    10→  - 9 providers: ANTHROPIC, OPENAI, OPENROUTER, NVIDIA_NIM, LOCAL, CLAUDE_CODE, CODEX, OPENROUTER_FREE, OLLAMA\n    11→  - ClaudeCodeProvider: spawns `claude -p` subprocesses — NOW respects per-agent model config (was hardcoded opus)\n    12→  - DEFAULT_CREW auto-detects: OPENROUTER if API key set (4 agents), else CLAUDE_CODE (3 agents)\n    13→  - OPENROUTER_API_KEY is set and working (llama-3.3-70b-instruct confirmed)\n    14→  - Each role gets 5-layer context injection (Vision/Research/Engineering/Ops/Swarm)\n    15→- **LIVE ORCHESTRATOR (`dgc orchestrate-live`)**: Concurrent asyncio launcher for all 5 systems:\n    16→  - Swarm loop (60s tick) — agent pool, task dispatch, coordination synthesis\n    17→  - Pulse loop (300s) — claude -p heartbeat with thread rotation + telos gates (skips inside Claude Code)\n    18→  - Evolution loop (600s) — periodic Darwin Engine archive monitoring\n    19→  - Health monitor (120s) — anomaly detection (agent_silent, failure_spike, throughput_drop)\n    20→  - Living layers (180s) — stigmergy decay, shakti perception, subconscious dreams\n    21→  - Env overrides: DGC_SWARM_TICK, DGC_PULSE_INTERVAL, DGC_EVOLUTION_INTERVAL, DGC_HEALTH_INTERVAL, DGC_LIVING_INTERVAL, DGC_MAX_DAILY\n    22→- **GENOME WIRED (Phase 1 complete)**:\n    23→  - Garden Daemon config in `daemon_config.py` (6h heartbeat, 5 threads, quiet hours 2-5, circuit breaker, rate limiting 4/day)\n    24→  - v7 induction rules auto-injected into every agent's system_prompt\n    25→  - 5 PSMV roles: CARTOGRAPHER, ARCHEOLOGIST, SURGEON, ARCHITECT, VALIDATOR + RESEARCHER scouts\n    26→  - Role briefings from PSMV loaded per-role\n    27→  - Thread rotation in `thread_manager.py` (sequential/random/continuation, state persists)\n    28→  - Human overrides: `.PAUSE`, `.FOCUS`, `.INJECT` files\n    29→  - 5-layer context engine in `context.py` (Vision->Research->Engineering->Ops->Swarm, 30K budget, role-weighted)\n    30→- **Execution gap FIXED**: Tasks now actually fire `runner.run_task()` via `asyncio.create_task()`, not just bookkeeping\n    31→- **v0.2.0 OVERNIGHT BUILD (2026-03-05)**: 11 new modules + integration tests, built by 12 parallel agents:\n    32→  - **archive.py** (217 lines): FitnessScore, ArchiveEntry, EvolutionArchive (JSONL, lineage tracking)\n    33→  - **file_lock.py** (389 lines): AsyncFileLock (fcntl.flock via asyncio.to_thread), AsyncLockManager (sorted acquisition)\n    34→  - **elegance.py** (345 lines): AST-based code quality scoring (cyclomatic complexity, nesting, docstrings, naming)\n    35→  - **metrics.py** (412 lines): BehavioralSignature, MetricsAnalyzer (entropy, complexity, swabhaav_ratio, mimicry detection)\n    36→  - **fitness_predictor.py** (184 lines): Historical-based fitness prediction by (component, change_type) groups\n    37→  - **selector.py** (191 lines): 4 parent selection strategies (tournament, roulette, rank, elite)\n    38→  - **traces.py** (184 lines): TraceStore with atomic JSON writes, lineage traversal, archive rotation\n    39→  - **rv.py** (258 lines): RVReading, RVMeasurer (lazy torch), compute_participation_ratio (SVD-based)\n    40→  - **evolution.py** (447 lines): DarwinEngine orchestrating PROPOSE->GATE->EVALUATE->ARCHIVE->SELECT\n    41→  - **monitor.py** (353 lines): SystemMonitor, anomaly detection (failure_spike, agent_silent, throughput_drop)\n    42→  - **bridge.py** (427 lines): ResearchBridge correlating R_V with behavioral signatures (Pearson r, Spearman rho)\n    43→  - **swarm.py wired**: evolve(), health_check(), fitness_trend() methods added\n    44→  - **cli.py wired**: `evolve propose`, `evolve trend`, `health` commands added\n    45→  - **31 integration tests** across 5 categories (evolution pipeline, monitor+traces, bridge+metrics, cross-system, edge cases)\n    46→- **Key integration doc**: `~/dharma_swarm/GENOME_WIRING.md`\n    47→- **Daemon launcher**: `bash ~/dharma_swarm/run_daemon.sh` (PID at `~/.dharma/daemon.pid`)\n    48→- **Phase 2 remaining**: Genome Tier A (6 hard tests), Tier B (MAP-Elites), duplicate detection, debate chamber, parasite tournament\n    49→- **Relationship to dgc-core**: dharma_swarm is the EXECUTION layer; dgc-core is the CONTEXT/MEMORY layer; PSMV is the KNOWLEDGE layer\n    50→- **v0.3 Bug Sweep (2026-03-08)**: 25+ bugs fixed across 90+ source + 45 test + 35 script files. **1731 tests, 0 failures.** Key: TOCTOU races, connection leaks, zombie processes, corrupt JSON handling, file handle leaks, missing protocol methods.\n    51→- **Architecture layers**: models.py (schema) -> providers.py (LLM) -> agent_runner.py (lifecycle) -> orchestrator.py (routing) -> swarm.py (facade)\n    52→- **Subpackages**: engine/ (artifact-centric orchestration, 7 files), tui/ (refactored Textual UI, 28 files, 4357 lines), tui_legacy.py (old monolith)\n    53→- **Additional modules**: adaptive_autonomy.py, canary.py, policy_compiler.py, providers_extended.py, signal_map.py, skills.py, handoff.py, anekanta_gate.py, dogma_gate.py, steelman_gate.py, shakti.py, subconscious.py\n    54→- **v0.4.0-v0.4.2 Oz Evolution (2026-03-08)**: 14 new modules, ~4,500+ lines source, ~200+ tests\n    55→  - **v0.4.0**: skills.py, profiles.py, intent_router.py (TF-IDF semantic), context_search.py, adaptive_autonomy.py\n    56→  - **v0.4.1**: skill_composer.py (DAG), handoff.py (A2A artifacts), agent_memory.py (Letta 3-tier)\n    57→  - **v0.4.2 (Oz P0-P2)**: diff_applier.py (unified diff + rollback), dag_executor.py (wave execution), sleep_cycle.py (4-phase consolidation)\n    58→  - **Production wiring**: DiffApplier->DarwinEngine (apply_diff_and_test), DAGExecutor->SwarmManager (execute_composition), SleepCycle->pulse.py (quiet hours), message_bus artifacts\n    59→  - **CLI**: skills, route, orchestrate, autonomy, context-search, compose, execute-compose, handoff, agent-memory\n    60→  - **Agent memory in runner**: AgentRunner accepts AgentMemoryBank, auto-injects context, auto-learns from task success/failure\n    61→"}]},"uuid":"fa73c56a-8c7b-41bc-9643-a505e88805d7","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:17:58.358Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"91a9e5b2-e119-43b9-9f31-0cc0f63ce4ac","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
