{"parentUuid":"812e2bbb-4e25-44b9-acef-27742fbc5c12","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"a6199312c888fb590","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013eXdenTCpPdh8AwN5pMdyb","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Anthropic Constitutional AI Claude 2026 strategy safety research\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Anthropic\",\"url\":\"https://www.anthropic.com/news/claudes-constitution\"},{\"title\":\"Claude's New Constitution: AI Alignment, Ethics, and the Future of Model Governance — Bloomsbury Intelligence and Security Institute (BISI)\",\"url\":\"https://bisi.org.uk/reports/claudes-new-constitution-ai-alignment-ethics-and-the-future-of-model-governance\"},{\"title\":\"Anthropic Publishes Claude AI's New Constitution | TIME\",\"url\":\"https://time.com/7354738/claude-constitution-ai-alignment/\"},{\"title\":\"Anthropic revises Claude's 'Constitution,' and hints at chatbot consciousness | TechCrunch\",\"url\":\"https://techcrunch.com/2026/01/21/anthropic-revises-claudes-constitution-and-hints-at-chatbot-consciousness/\"},{\"title\":\"Anthropic rewrites Claude’s guiding principles—and reckons with the possibility of AI consciousness | Fortune\",\"url\":\"https://fortune.com/2026/01/21/anthropic-claude-ai-chatbot-new-rules-safety-consciousness/\"},{\"title\":\"Anthropic’s Claude AI gets a new constitution embedding safety and ethics | CIO\",\"url\":\"https://www.cio.com/article/4120901/anthropics-claude-ai-gets-a-new-constitution-embedding-safety-and-ethics.html\"},{\"title\":\"Amazon.com: Claude 4 (Anthropic): Safety-First Frontier AI in 2026: Architecture Applications, Governance and Future Horizons for Education Research and Professional ... AI Tools transforming life skills Book 1) eBook : Mishra, Anshuman: Kindle Store\",\"url\":\"https://www.amazon.com/Claude-Anthropic-Safety-First-Architecture-Applications-ebook/dp/B0GQZVZ3PX\"},{\"title\":\"Anthropic’s Approach to Safe AI\",\"url\":\"https://aishwaryasrinivasan.substack.com/p/anthropics-approach-to-safe-ai\"},{\"title\":\"Constitutional Classifiers: Defending against universal jailbreaks \\\\ Anthropic\",\"url\":\"https://www.anthropic.com/research/constitutional-classifiers\"},{\"title\":\"Anthropic releases new AI ‘constitution’ for Claude - SiliconANGLE\",\"url\":\"https://siliconangle.com/2026/01/21/anthropic-releases-new-ai-constitution-claude/\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about Anthropic's Constitutional AI, Claude, and their 2026 strategy for safety research:\n\n## Claude's New Constitution (January 2026)\n\nAnthropic published a comprehensive new constitution for Claude on 22 January 2026, shifting from rule-based to reason-based AI alignment that explains the logic behind ethical principles rather than prescribing specific behaviours.\n\n### Key Features of the New Constitution\n\nThe framework establishes a 4-tier priority hierarchy (safety, ethics, compliance, helpfulness) and becomes the first major AI company document to formally acknowledge the possibility of AI consciousness and moral status.\n\nThe AI lab is moving away from training the model to follow a simple list of principles—such as choosing the response that is least racist or sexist—to instead teach the AI why it should act in certain ways. This represents a significant shift in approach compared to Anthropic's previous constitution, published in 2023, which was a list of principles drawn from sources like the UN Universal Declaration of Human Rights and Apple's terms of service.\n\n### Constitutional AI Approach\n\nConstitutional AI provides one answer by giving language models explicit values determined by a constitution, rather than values determined implicitly via large-scale human feedback. Instead of just saying, 'here's a bunch of behaviors that we want,' Anthropic is hoping that if you give models the reasons why you want these behaviors, it's going to generalize more effectively in new contexts.\n\n### Safety Research and Regulatory Alignment\n\nAnthropic signed the EU General-Purpose AI Code of Practice in July 2025, which provides a presumption of conformity, reducing administrative burden as full enforcement begins in August 2026 with penalties reaching EUR 35m or 7% of global revenue.\n\nThe new constitution also takes an unprecedented step in acknowledging uncertainty: Anthropic acknowledges uncertainty about whether the AI might have \"some kind of consciousness or moral status,\" saying it cares about Claude's \"psychological security, sense of self, and well-being,\" both for Claude's sake and because these qualities may affect its judgment and safety.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"a77238bc-da2d-42c6-bd49-2b5e0f1f4d9c","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:18:14.104Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"812e2bbb-4e25-44b9-acef-27742fbc5c12","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
