{"parentUuid":"7f2cbd05-ebbf-4294-8db2-a86af80bb6a6","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a6199312c888fb590","type":"progress","data":{"type":"hook_progress","hookEvent":"PostToolUse","hookName":"PostToolUse:WebSearch","command":"bash \"${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/scripts/hooks/run-with-flags-shell.sh\" \"post:observe\" \"skills/continuous-learning-v2/hooks/observe.sh\" \"standard,strict\""},"parentToolUseID":"toolu_01GfYtX4cCw57YshkJX7dWXF","toolUseID":"toolu_01GfYtX4cCw57YshkJX7dWXF","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:18:26.525Z","uuid":"1e00c46a-7034-4243-ab18-262430caf962","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"e169e3e3-2605-4761-9fc8-08d60b26b5b0","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"a6199312c888fb590","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GfYtX4cCw57YshkJX7dWXF","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Meta Llama open source AI strategy 2026 Mark Zuckerberg\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Open Source AI is the Path Forward\",\"url\":\"https://about.fb.com/news/2024/07/open-source-ai-is-the-path-forward/\"},{\"title\":\"Mark Zuckerberg Just Intensified the Battle For AI’s Future | TIME\",\"url\":\"https://time.com/7002563/mark-zuckerberg-ai-llama-meta-open-source/\"},{\"title\":\"From Llamas to Avocados: Meta's shifting AI strategy is causing internal confusion\",\"url\":\"https://www.cnbc.com/2025/12/09/meta-avocado-ai-strategy-issues.html\"},{\"title\":\"Mark Zuckerberg and the Drive Towards AI Superintelligence | AI Magazine\",\"url\":\"https://aimagazine.com/news/mark-zuckerberg-top-100-ai-leaders-2026\"},{\"title\":\"How Mark Zuckerberg has rebuilt Meta around Llama, pivoting the whole company towards generative AI\",\"url\":\"https://sharongoldman.substack.com/p/how-mark-zuckerberg-has-rebuilt-meta\"},{\"title\":\"How Meta’s Open Source AI is Giving US the Edge in AI Race | Technology Magazine\",\"url\":\"https://technologymagazine.com/articles/how-metas-open-source-ai-is-giving-us-the-edge-in-ai-race\"},{\"title\":\"How Mark Zuckerberg has fully rebuilt Meta around Llama\",\"url\":\"https://finance.yahoo.com/news/mark-zuckerberg-went-meta-major-103000635.html\"},{\"title\":\"How Mark Zuckerberg went all-in to make Meta a major AI player and threaten OpenAI’s dominance | Fortune\",\"url\":\"https://fortune.com/2024/11/19/zuckerberg-meta-ai-openai-llama/\"},{\"title\":\"Inside Meta’s Pivot From Open Source to Money-Making AI Model - Articles - Advisor Perspectives\",\"url\":\"https://www.advisorperspectives.com/articles/2025/12/10/inside-metas-pivot-open-source-money-making-ai-model\"},{\"title\":\"Meta reportedly delays Llama successor, shifts to closed-source AI amid internal reorganization\",\"url\":\"https://www.digitimes.com/news/a20251211PD206/meta-llama-development-2026.html\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about Meta's Llama open source AI strategy and Mark Zuckerberg's approach in 2026:\n\n## Meta's Open Source AI Strategy\n\nMeta is committed to open source AI, with Zuckerberg outlining why he believes open source is the best development stack, why open sourcing Llama is good for Meta, and why open source AI is good for the world.\n\nThe path for Llama to become the industry standard is by being consistently competitive, efficient, and open generation after generation. In 2025, the company launched the fourth iteration of its Llama large language model (LLM) family, introducing Scout and Maverick, alongside a preview of the much larger Behemoth, designed for tasks ranging from enterprise applications to content creation and multimodal processing.\n\n## Strategic Shift and 2026 Developments\n\nHowever, Meta's strategy is undergoing significant changes. Meta is pursuing a new Llama successor and frontier AI model, codenamed Avocado, with plans for release in the first quarter of 2026. One new model, codenamed Avocado, is expected to debut sometime next spring, and may be launched as a \"closed\" model — one that can be tightly controlled and that Meta can sell access to, which would mark the biggest departure to date from the open-source strategy Meta has touted for years.\n\nIn July 2025, Mark Zuckerberg reportedly confirmed that Meta would not release models capable of superintelligence as open-source.\n\n## Leadership and Investment\n\nZuckerberg hired Scale AI's 28-year-old CEO Alexandr Wang as Meta's new chief AI officer and head of an elite unit called TBD Lab, with Avocado's release planned for the first quarter of 2026. Zuckerberg has pledged to spend $600 billion on US infrastructure projects over the next three years, most of them AI-related.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"30774960-3f1f-4dd2-8fc4-f686e5e69541","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:18:26.524Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"e169e3e3-2605-4761-9fc8-08d60b26b5b0","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
