{"parentUuid":"6996eba9-8e6b-432f-a858-a76189d946f1","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"a6199312c888fb590","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016oWjBxfiFBj36FwU7mH43y","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"AI agent frameworks 2026 MCP protocol agentic systems landscape\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"15 MCP Use Cases Powering the Future of Agentic AI 2026\",\"url\":\"https://onereach.ai/whitepapers/mcp-use-cases-for-agentic-ai/\"},{\"title\":\"MCP vs A2A: The Complete Guide to AI Agent Protocols in 2026 - DEV Community\",\"url\":\"https://dev.to/pockit_tools/mcp-vs-a2a-the-complete-guide-to-ai-agent-protocols-in-2026-30li\"},{\"title\":\"Top 5 Open Protocols for Building Multi-Agent AI Systems 2026\",\"url\":\"https://onereach.ai/blog/power-of-multi-agent-ai-open-protocols/\"},{\"title\":\"Top 5 Open-Source Agentic AI Frameworks in 2026\",\"url\":\"https://aimultiple.com/agentic-frameworks\"},{\"title\":\"5 Key Trends Shaping Agentic Development in 2026 - The New Stack\",\"url\":\"https://thenewstack.io/5-key-trends-shaping-agentic-development-in-2026/\"},{\"title\":\"AI Spotlight: MCP (Model Context Protocol) and Agentic AI systems\",\"url\":\"https://www.gravitee.io/blog/mcp-model-context-protocol-agentic-ai\"},{\"title\":\"AI Agent Protocols 2026: The Complete Guide to Standardizing AI Communication\",\"url\":\"https://www.ruh.ai/blogs/ai-agent-protocols-2026-complete-guide\"},{\"title\":\"The Model Context Protocol: The Architecture of Agentic Intelligence | by Greg Robison | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://gregrobison.medium.com/the-model-context-protocol-the-architecture-of-agentic-intelligence-cfc0e4613c1e\"},{\"title\":\"Why the Agentic AI Foundation (AAIF) Changes Everything for MCP — And Why Enterprises Need Secure Agentic Infrastructure | Solo.io\",\"url\":\"https://www.solo.io/blog/aaif-announcement-agentgateway\"},{\"title\":\"The rise of agentic AI part 1: Understanding MCP, A2A, and the future of automation\",\"url\":\"https://www.dynatrace.com/news/blog/agentic-ai-how-mcp-and-ai-agents-drive-the-latest-automation-revolution/\"}]\n\nHere's a comprehensive overview of the AI agent frameworks and MCP protocol landscape in 2026:\n\n## Model Context Protocol (MCP) Overview\n\nMCP, created by Anthropic and donated to the Linux Foundation's Agentic AI Foundation (AAIF) in December 2025, standardizes how an AI agent connects to external tools, data sources, and services. It serves as the standard interface between an AI brain and its hands.\n\nMCP acts as a universal connector for AI systems — often described as the \"USB-C of AI connectivity.\" With MCP, time-to-integration drops from months to weeks, and development costs can be reduced by up to 70%.\n\n## Governance and Ecosystem\n\nThe Linux Foundation launched the Agentic AI Foundation (AAIF) in December 2025 — co-founded by OpenAI, Anthropic, Google, Microsoft, AWS, and Block — as the permanent home for both A2A and MCP. By February 2026, MCP has crossed 97 million monthly SDK downloads (Python + TypeScript combined) and has been adopted by every major AI provider.\n\n## Related Protocols\n\nFor those looking to build scalable multi-agent AI systems, it's essential to understand five key protocols: MCP (Model Context Protocol), ACP (Agent Communication Protocol), A2A (Agent-to-Agent Protocol), ANP (Agent Network Protocol), and AG-UI (Agent-User Interaction Protocol).\n\nA2A (Agent-to-Agent), created by Google in April 2025 and donated to the Linux Foundation in June 2025, standardizes how AI agents discover, communicate, and collaborate with each other — regarded as HTTP for AI agents.\n\n## Agentic Framework Integration\n\nMost frameworks support Model-Context-Protocol (MCP), either natively or through community extensions. Key frameworks with MCP integration include LangGraph, AutoGen, CrewAI, OpenAI Swarm, and LangChain.\n\n## Enterprise Impact\n\nMcKinsey's 2025 AI State Report found that organizations using multi-agent systems achieve 3x higher ROI than single-agent implementations. MCP-based agentic AI systems boost productivity by 35–40% within the first six months of implementation.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"460d8a62-a9dc-4b74-90ee-2486fe3a665e","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:18:27.242Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"6996eba9-8e6b-432f-a858-a76189d946f1","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
