{"parentUuid":"0ea50fc5-43da-4a0d-9cdb-1a37173c77d5","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"a6199312c888fb590","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01991CW9CAfqitzUoWREzVRj","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Sakana AI self-improving agents 2026 Darwin Gödel Machine research\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"The Darwin Gödel Machine: AI that improves itself by rewriting its own code\",\"url\":\"https://sakana.ai/dgm/\"},{\"title\":\"Sakana AI on X: \\\"Introducing The Darwin Gödel Machine: AI that improves itself by rewriting its own code https://t.co/tBzlhoUMZO The Darwin Gödel Machine (DGM) is a self-improving agent that can modify its own code. Inspired by evolution, we maintain an expanding lineage of agent variants, https://t.co/yIQ0w85N7U\\\" / X\",\"url\":\"https://x.com/SakanaAILabs/status/1928272612431646943\"},{\"title\":\"Sakana AI's Darwin-Gödel Machine evolves by rewriting its own code to boost performance\",\"url\":\"https://the-decoder.com/sakana-ais-darwin-godel-machine-evolves-by-rewriting-its-own-code-to-boost-performance/\"},{\"title\":\"[2505.22954] Darwin Godel Machine: Open-Ended Evolution of Self-Improving Agents\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/abs/2505.22954\"},{\"title\":\"Darwin-Gödel Machine: The First Self-Improving AI System Is Here\",\"url\":\"https://www.intoai.pub/p/darwin-godel-machine-the-first-self\"},{\"title\":\"Sakana AI on X: \\\"Read our paper: “Darwin Godel Machine: Open-Ended Evolution of Self-Improving Agents” https://t.co/Ej2KIkEXdh We believe that Darwin Gödel Machines represent a concrete step towards AI systems that can autonomously gather their own stepping stones to learn and innovate forever! https://t.co/RUDBZ34wWU\\\" / X\",\"url\":\"https://x.com/SakanaAILabs/status/1928352742147510319\"},{\"title\":\"Sakana AI Unveils Darwin Gödel Machine: The Self-Improving AI Rewriting Its Own Code\",\"url\":\"https://www.startuphub.ai/sakana-ai-unveils-darwin-godel-machine-the-self-improving-ai-rewriting-its-own-code/\"},{\"title\":\"The Sequence Research #673: Infinite Self-Improvement: Unpacking Sakana's Darwin Gödel Machine\",\"url\":\"https://thesequence.substack.com/p/the-sequence-research-673-infinite\"},{\"title\":\"Darwin Gödel Machine: Open-Ended Evolution of Self-Improving Agents | SuperIntelligence - Robotics - Safety & Alignment\",\"url\":\"https://s-rsa.com/index.php/agi/article/view/15063\"},{\"title\":\"The Darwin Gödel Machine: AI That Evolves by Rewriting Its Own Code | by Robert Encarnacao | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://medium.com/@delimiterbob/the-darwin-g%C3%B6del-machine-ai-that-evolves-by-rewriting-its-own-code-8088be8ca3a5\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about Sakana AI's Darwin Gödel Machine research:\n\n## Overview\n\nThe Darwin Gödel Machine is a self-improving coding agent that rewrites its own code to improve performance on programming tasks. Researchers at Sakana AI and the University of British Columbia developed the Darwin-Gödel Machine (DGM), an AI framework designed to evolve on its own.\n\n## How It Works\n\nThe Darwin Gödel Machine is a self-improving system that iteratively modifies its own code (thereby also improving its ability to modify its own codebase) and empirically validates each change using coding benchmarks. DGMs leverage foundation models to propose code improvements, and use recent innovations in open-ended algorithms to search for a growing library of diverse, high-quality AI agents.\n\n## Performance Results\n\nThe system has demonstrated impressive improvements on coding benchmarks:\n\n- On SWE-bench, DGM automatically improved its performance from 20.0% to 50.0%, and on Polyglot, the DGM increased its success rate from an initial 14.2% to 30.7%, significantly outperforming representative hand-designed agents.\n\n## Key Features and Improvements\n\nThe system developed several key features on its own—new editing tools, a patch verification step, the ability to evaluate multiple solution proposals, and an error memory to avoid repeating past mistakes. The improved tools and workflows discovered by DGM generalized across different foundation models, with an agent optimized with Claude 3.5 Sonnet showing performance gains when subsequently powered by o3-mini or Claude 3.7 Sonnet.\n\n## Theoretical Foundation\n\nThe Gödel machine proposed a theoretical alternative: a self-improving AI that repeatedly modifies itself in a provably beneficial manner, but proving that most changes are net beneficial is impossible in practice. The Darwin Gödel Machine addresses this by using empirical validation rather than formal proofs.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"41d8e6e5-d6e0-409e-8c00-696d71196c51","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:18:27.705Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"0ea50fc5-43da-4a0d-9cdb-1a37173c77d5","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
