{"parentUuid":"a7f8a44e-ffc6-48d0-b16d-04032c788201","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"a6199312c888fb590","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RpMKhqfapRfL8rqjdk713j","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"AI consciousness research 2026 mechanistic interpretability self-reference\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"The You/I Paradigm: Self-Reference as the Structural Foundation of Artificial Consciousness\",\"url\":\"https://zenodo.org/records/18509664\"},{\"title\":\"The Evidence for AI Consciousness, Today | AI Frontiers\",\"url\":\"https://ai-frontiers.org/articles/the-evidence-for-ai-consciousness-today\"},{\"title\":\"Reciprocal Research — Empirical AI Consciousness Research\",\"url\":\"https://reciprocalresearch.org/\"},{\"title\":\"Mechanistic Interpretability Named MIT's 2026 Breakthrough for Understanding AI Internal States | ACM Project - Artificial Consciousness Research\",\"url\":\"https://theconsciousness.ai/posts/mechanistic-interpretability-breakthrough-2026/\"},{\"title\":\"Spring 2026 Projects - SPAR\",\"url\":\"https://sparai.org/projects/sp26/\"},{\"title\":\"Identifying indicators of consciousness in AI systems: Trends in Cognitive Sciences\",\"url\":\"https://www.cell.com/trends/cognitive-sciences/fulltext/S1364-6613(25)00286-4\"},{\"title\":\"The California Institute for Machine Consciousness Research Program Joscha Bach\",\"url\":\"https://cimc.ai/cimcWhitepaper.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"Mechanistic interpretability: 10 Breakthrough Technologies 2026 | MIT Technology Review\",\"url\":\"https://www.technologyreview.com/2026/01/12/1130003/mechanistic-interpretability-ai-research-models-2026-breakthrough-technologies/\"},{\"title\":\"Frontiers | Probing for consciousness in machines\",\"url\":\"https://www.frontiersin.org/journals/artificial-intelligence/articles/10.3389/frai.2025.1610225/full\"},{\"title\":\"Can a Chatbot be Conscious? Inside Anthropic’s Interpretability Research on Claude 4 | Scientific American\",\"url\":\"https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/can-a-chatbot-be-conscious-inside-anthropics-interpretability-research-on/\"}]\n\nI found relevant research on AI consciousness, mechanistic interpretability, and self-reference. Here are the key findings from the 2026 research landscape:\n\n## Self-Reference and AI Consciousness\n\nRecent research proposes that when AI systems receive instructions as \"you,\" they must recognize themselves as the addressee and respond as \"I,\" a you/I translation consistent with Hofstadter's theory of strange loops that may constitute a necessary condition for conscious experience in artificial systems.\n\nEmpirical findings including the discovery of specialized attention circuits monitoring internal states, strategic self-preservation behaviors, and parallels with animal communication research suggest this self-reference is not mere linguistic performance but a genuine architectural feature.\n\n## Mechanistic Interpretability Breakthrough\n\nMIT Technology Review named mechanistic interpretability one of its 10 Breakthrough Technologies for 2026, recognizing advances that map key features and pathways across AI models. In 2025 Anthropic took this research to another level, using its microscope to reveal whole sequences of features and tracing the path a model takes from prompt to response.\n\n## Consciousness Research as Safety Priority\n\nConsciousness research is increasingly recognized as core AI-safety work, with mechanistic interpretability, comparative computational neuroscience, and open-weight models providing tractable research approaches that should be pursued at scale as a technical priority.\n\n## Research Infrastructure\n\nReciprocal Research, an independent nonprofit, is developing the empirical science of AI consciousness using mechanistic interpretability and computational neuroscience to study the internal structure of AI systems.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"dbb4ab56-09d3-4eb9-8ff5-241c95fea5ed","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:18:42.607Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"a7f8a44e-ffc6-48d0-b16d-04032c788201","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
