{"parentUuid":"83affc9b-e39c-4c4e-9cab-e5d55cef275a","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"a6199312c888fb590","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HQ852UuKbLgpq95oT3PPcs","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"AI alignment telos purpose values 2026 beyond safety profit ethical frameworks\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"RESEARCH PAPER JANUARY 2026 Legal Alignment for Safe and Ethical AI\",\"url\":\"https://aigi.ox.ac.uk/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/Kolt-Caputo-et-al.-2026-Legal-Alignment-for-Safe-and-Ethical-AI.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"Teaching AI Ethics 2026: Power\",\"url\":\"https://leonfurze.com/2026/02/02/teaching-ai-ethics-2026-power/\"},{\"title\":\"AI value alignment: Aligning AI with human values | World Economic Forum\",\"url\":\"https://www.weforum.org/stories/2024/10/ai-value-alignment-how-we-can-align-artificial-intelligence-with-human-values/\"},{\"title\":\"How we think about safety and alignment | OpenAI\",\"url\":\"https://openai.com/safety/how-we-think-about-safety-alignment/\"},{\"title\":\"Hype and harm: Why we must ask harder questions about AI and its alignment with human values | Brookings\",\"url\":\"https://www.brookings.edu/articles/hype-and-harm-why-we-must-ask-harder-questions-about-ai-and-its-alignment-with-human-values/\"},{\"title\":\"AI Moral Alignment: The Most Important Goal of Our Generation — EA Forum\",\"url\":\"https://forum.effectivealtruism.org/posts/4LimpA4pyLemxN4BF/ai-moral-alignment-the-most-important-goal-of-our-generation\"},{\"title\":\"What Is AI Alignment? Principles, Challenges & Solutions - WitnessAI\",\"url\":\"https://witness.ai/blog/ai-alignment/\"},{\"title\":\"ValueCompass: A Framework of Fundamental Values for Human-AI Alignment\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/html/2409.09586v1\"},{\"title\":\"AI Safety, Alignment, and Interpretability in 2026 | Zylos Research\",\"url\":\"https://zylos.ai/research/2026-02-09-ai-safety-alignment-interpretability\"},{\"title\":\"Top AI ethics and policy issues of 2025 and what to expect in 2026 - ΑΙhub\",\"url\":\"https://aihub.org/2026/03/04/top-ai-ethics-and-policy-issues-of-2025-and-what-to-expect-in-2026/\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what current discussions reveal about AI alignment, values, and ethical frameworks beyond just safety considerations:\n\n## AI Alignment Beyond Safety and Profit\n\nAI alignment encompasses both the normative problem of specifying which values are desirable or appropriate for AI systems and the technical problem of ensuring AI systems give effect to those values when making decisions and taking actions.\n\nHowever, most alignment techniques train AI systems to comply with company-written alignment policies or satisfy the revealed preferences of individual users through methods such as reinforcement learning from human feedback, rather than addressing broader societal values.\n\n## Expanded Ethical Frameworks\n\nRecent discussions extend beyond traditional safety concerns:\n\n**Moral Alignment and Sentience**: Traditional AI alignment often ignores the ethical implications for all sentient beings, while Moral Alignment as part of the broader AI alignment space is focused on the values we aim to instill in AI.\n\n**Legal and Democratic Values**: A central component of this challenge involves designing AI systems that are aligned with human interests and democratic values.\n\n**Context and Diversity**: AI alignment must be context-sensitive, transparent, adaptable and aligned with local requirements, reflecting diverse cultural and societal values.\n\n## 2026 Strategic Shifts\n\n2026 may become the year when restraint becomes a strategic necessity rather than just a moral choice, as AI capabilities have advanced faster than institutions and governance frameworks could adapt. Autonomy, sovereignty, and sustainability may take center stage, with three pressures likely to dominate: governing increasingly automated systems, managing economic and workforce disruption, and confronting environmental and infrastructural limits.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"6bbd8689-a7b8-403c-9a21-962447e1d62a","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:18:53.901Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"83affc9b-e39c-4c4e-9cab-e5d55cef275a","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
