{"parentUuid":"2965ecf8-7d2c-41bf-8707-33d3ab3e06f7","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a6199312c888fb590","type":"progress","data":{"type":"hook_progress","hookEvent":"PostToolUse","hookName":"PostToolUse:WebSearch","command":"bash \"${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/scripts/hooks/run-with-flags-shell.sh\" \"post:observe\" \"skills/continuous-learning-v2/hooks/observe.sh\" \"standard,strict\""},"parentToolUseID":"toolu_01Xi5STosg89YhpjoALP3suH","toolUseID":"toolu_01Xi5STosg89YhpjoALP3suH","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:19:04.748Z","uuid":"cb5c7a91-ff1b-45bd-a187-42de9c65e7d3","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"b23227ab-1a92-411a-b7ac-6fc4de27c504","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"a6199312c888fb590","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Xi5STosg89YhpjoALP3suH","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Groq inference chips 2026 Together AI Mistral efficiency infrastructure\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Nvidia GTC 2026: AI Chip Pivot & $20B Groq Bet\",\"url\":\"https://theoutpost.ai/news-story/nvidia-faces-mounting-ai-chip-competition-as-gtc-2026-showcases-groq-integration-and-new-hardware-24557/\"},{\"title\":\"Best Inference Providers for AI Agents in 2026 | Fast.io\",\"url\":\"https://fast.io/resources/best-inference-providers-ai-agents/\"},{\"title\":\"Build Groq Compound AI: Mixture-of-Agents Inference 2026 | Markaicode\",\"url\":\"https://markaicode.com/groq-compound-ai-mixture-of-agents-inference/\"},{\"title\":\"Groq Review 2026 | AI Infrastructure & MLOps Tool - Pricing & Features\",\"url\":\"https://aiagentslist.com/agents/groq\"},{\"title\":\"What’s Groq AI and Everything About LPU [2026]\",\"url\":\"https://www.voiceflow.com/blog/groq\"},{\"title\":\"Groq Inference Tokenomics: Speed, But At What Cost?\",\"url\":\"https://newsletter.semianalysis.com/p/groq-inference-tokenomics-speed-but\"},{\"title\":\"Groq is fast, low cost inference.\",\"url\":\"https://groq.com/\"},{\"title\":\"NVIDIA CEO Jensen Huang to Outline AI Inference Push at GTC 2026 Keynote | Technobezz\",\"url\":\"https://www.technobezz.com/news/nvidia-ceo-jensen-huang-to-outline-ai-inference-push-at-gtc-2026-keynote\"},{\"title\":\"What is Groq? Features, Pricing, and Use Cases\",\"url\":\"https://www.walturn.com/insights/what-is-groq-features-pricing-and-use-cases\"},{\"title\":\"Nvidia, Groq and the limestone race to real-time AI: Why enterprises win or lose here | VentureBeat\",\"url\":\"https://venturebeat.com/infrastructure/nvidia-groq-and-the-limestone-race-to-real-time-ai-why-enterprises-win-or\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about Groq inference chips, Together AI, and Mistral in 2026:\n\n## Groq Inference Technology\n\nGroq pioneered the LPU (Language Processing Unit) in 2016, the first chip purpose-built for inference. Groq optimizes for latency (time to first token) with its LPU architecture, achieving sub-100ms responses. Groq's LPU architecture removes the memory bandwidth bottleneck that plagues GPUs during small-batch inference, delivering lightning-fast inference.\n\nGroq can run Llama 3.3 70B at 750+ tokens/sec. The chips are designed to offer deterministic execution, which allows for highly predictable latency and throughput.\n\n## Together AI and Open Models\n\nTogether AI excels at open-weight models (Llama, Mistral, Mixtral) with 200+ models and sub-100ms latency. Together AI offers high-performance inference for 200+ open-source LLMs with sub-100ms latency, automated tuning, and horizontal scaling.\n\n## Infrastructure and Efficiency\n\nGroq's architecture is up to 10× more energy-efficient than conventional GPU-based deployments, reducing both carbon footprint and operational costs.\n\n## 2026 Industry Context\n\nNvidia's annual GTC developer conference begins with CEO Jensen Huang expected to detail the company's $20 billion Groq acquisition and showcase how CPUs are becoming critical for agentic AI workloads. A pre-show event includes CEOs from Perplexity, LangChain, Mistral, Skild AI and OpenEvidence discussing industry developments.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"7e69aba7-830a-4732-bfff-1233b05585d3","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:19:04.748Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"b23227ab-1a92-411a-b7ac-6fc4de27c504","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"7e69aba7-830a-4732-bfff-1233b05585d3","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a6199312c888fb590","type":"progress","data":{"type":"hook_progress","hookEvent":"PostToolUse","hookName":"PostToolUse:WebSearch","command":"bash \"${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/scripts/hooks/run-with-flags-shell.sh\" \"post:observe\" \"skills/continuous-learning-v2/hooks/observe.sh\" \"standard,strict\""},"parentToolUseID":"toolu_013nsCjNDR37gFo2jwxQ1Rjp","toolUseID":"toolu_013nsCjNDR37gFo2jwxQ1Rjp","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:19:06.356Z","uuid":"000f5ed0-1787-4f26-a7c5-d3afad9ae4f3","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"d8d899ab-4f61-4806-b44f-4692ac6b86b5","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"a6199312c888fb590","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013nsCjNDR37gFo2jwxQ1Rjp","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"\"ontology first\" vs \"data lake\" AI architecture 2026 knowledge graphs semantic layer\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Ontologies, Context Graphs, and Semantic Layers: What AI Actually Needs in 2026\",\"url\":\"https://metadataweekly.substack.com/p/ontologies-context-graphs-and-semantic\"},{\"title\":\"Knowledge Graph vs Ontology: Know Differences\",\"url\":\"https://www.puppygraph.com/blog/knowledge-graph-vs-ontology\"},{\"title\":\"GraphRAG & Knowledge Graphs: Making Your Data AI-Ready for 2026 - Fluree\",\"url\":\"https://flur.ee/fluree-blog/graphrag-knowledge-graphs-making-your-data-ai-ready-for-2026/\"},{\"title\":\"Semantic Layers in 2025: A Catalog Owner and Data Leader Playbook\",\"url\":\"https://coalesce.io/data-insights/semantic-layers-2025-catalog-owner-data-leader-playbook/\"},{\"title\":\"Biotech Knowledge Graphs: Architecture for Data Integration | IntuitionLabs\",\"url\":\"https://intuitionlabs.ai/articles/biotech-knowledge-graph-architecture\"},{\"title\":\"A survey on semantic data management as intersection of ontology-based data access, semantic modeling and data lakes - ScienceDirect\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1570826824000052\"},{\"title\":\"The Ontology issue: From knowledge to graphs and back again.\",\"url\":\"https://yearofthegraph.xyz/newsletter/2025/12/the-ontology-issue-from-knowledge-to-graphs-and-back-again-the-year-of-the-graph-newsletter-vol-29-winter-2025-2026/\"},{\"title\":\"Semantic Layers: The Missing Link Between AI and Business Insight | by Axel Schwanke | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://medium.com/@axel.schwanke/semantic-layers-the-missing-link-between-ai-and-business-insight-3c733f119be6\"},{\"title\":\"From RAG to GraphRAG: Knowledge Graphs, Ontologies and Smarter AI | GoodData\",\"url\":\"https://www.gooddata.com/blog/from-rag-to-graphrag-knowledge-graphs-ontologies-and-smarter-ai/\"},{\"title\":\"Semantic Web 3.0: Knowledge Graph Reasoning with Python for 2027 Data Lakes\",\"url\":\"https://johal.in/semantic-web-3-0-knowledge-graph-reasoning-with-python-for-2027-data-lakes-2/\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what current thinking shows about the \"ontology first\" versus \"data lake\" AI architecture debate in 2026:\n\n## Key Architectural Distinction\n\nOntologies are built for reasoning, helping systems and AI understand domains well enough to disambiguate data, discover context, make inferences, and support decisions, while semantic layers are built for analysis, helping humans consume data through BI tools, using natural language. Semantic layers and ontologies represent fundamentally different theories about what data systems are for—one optimizes for measurement, the other optimizes for meaning.\n\n## The Blended Approach Emerging in 2026\n\nRather than choosing between ontology-first and data lake approaches, the industry is moving toward integration. The trend of combining data lakes with semantic layers will grow, with tools that dynamically expose parts of a data lake as a graph through data virtualization maturing, and companies proposing multi-layer pipelines that start from raw lakes and progressively add ontology layers.\n\n## Role of Knowledge Graphs and Semantic Layers\n\nAn ontology can define the schema and semantics that guide the construction of a knowledge graph, while the knowledge graph provides the data that brings the ontology to life—with the ontology acting as the semantic backbone and the knowledge graph serving as the scalable, queryable data layer.\n\n## Division of Labor\n\nThe analytic semantic data layer is implemented in BI-native, platform-native, or universal/headless semantic layer tools on top of a warehouse or lakehouse, while the ontology/graph layer is implemented in semantic databases or graph systems, often managed by different teams.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"1103972c-fac5-43e4-891f-93021bb7b8e3","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:19:06.356Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"d8d899ab-4f61-4806-b44f-4692ac6b86b5","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
