{"parentUuid":"cb710261-b84b-49b3-8661-fdf7a1c3be4c","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"a6199312c888fb590","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013rkRnd9eKMiNKwd4RtGT9L","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# R_V Paper Status (Updated 2026-03-15)\n     2→\n     3→- **Skill for paper work**: use `rv-paper` skill — definitive knowledge base, honest framing, data file map\n     4→- **Target**: COLM 2026 (abstract Mar 26, paper Mar 31) — **11 DAYS to abstract**\n     5→- **Draft v007**: `~/mech-interp-latent-lab-phase1/R_V_PAPER/paper_colm2026_v007.tex` (1092 lines, 6186 words)\n     6→  - ALL 10 main sections + 8 appendices COMPLETE\n     7→  - **COLM 2026 TEMPLATE APPLIED** — uses colm2026_conference.sty (submission mode, line numbers)\n     8→  - 9pp main body + refs + 6pp appendix = 15pp total (FITS 9-page limit)\n     9→  - 7 figures now included (was 3): mode atlas, dissociation, cross-arch, layer sweep, safety ROC, safety genuine/deceptive, head sweep heatmap\n    10→  - **5 FABRICATED CITATIONS FIXED** (2026-03-11): dey->giorlandino (Giorlandino & Goldt), hong (correct authors), song (correct title+authors), berg (Cameron not Amanda), chun (correct title)\n    11→  - marks2023geometry duplicate DELETED, all 21 cited keys verified in bib\n    12→  - All 10 sections + 7 appendix sections, all numbers audited\n    13→  - Font note: local build uses CM (basic TeX Live); Overleaf will use proper Palatino\n    14→- **Title**: \"Geometric Signatures of Self-Referential Processing in Transformer Representations\" (DONE)\n    15→- **PHASE 0 CANONICALIZATION (2026-03-10/11) — MOSTLY COMPLETE**:\n    16→  - Title fixed: \"Representations\" not \"Value Spaces\"\n    17→  - d=-3.50 REMOVED (fabricated) -> behavioral transfer with dissociation (h=0.78, d=0.11 NS)\n    18→  - \"Four models\" -> \"two contract (GQA), two expand (MHA)\"\n    19→  - OPT/GPT-2: signed +d with honest expansion label\n    20→  - Necessity: L18 residual + L27 V-proj (not L25/L27), 56%->3.7% (not 27.7%)\n    21→  - Bridge: n1=80, n2=107 (not 150/150), p=9.2e-6\n    22→  - Table 1 n-values: OPT 72/66, GPT-2 69/56, Pythia 66/54, Qwen-3B 19/18\n    23→  - Qwen-3B d=1.60 (not 1.25)\n    24→  - statistical_hardening.py fully rewritten — loads ALL values from raw JSON\n    25→  - generate_paper_tables.py — LaTeX Table 1 from raw data with provenance\n    26→  - All 14 scripts patched to use PromptLoader (no inline prompts)\n    27→  - tests/test_rv_canonical.py — 43 tests, all passing\n    28→  - Qwen layer fix: 28 layers (not 32) in models.py + canonical_registry.json\n    29→  - Mistral-Instruct-v0.2 added to ModelSpec registry\n    30→  - Conclusion, discussion, limitations updated for honest framing\n    31→  - Multi-seed claim removed (d_std=0.0 is caching artifact)\n    32→  - **Overnight run COMPLETE (2026-03-10/11)**: head_sweep_n20, path_patching (32x3), dual_layer_bridge (n=300)\n    33→    - Path patching: Residual dominates L0-L5 (d~1.7-1.9), V-proj max d=0.77 (L5 only), MLP negligible\n    34→    - Head sweep: Top heads L22.H21 (d_ent=-7.23), L24.H09 (-4.97), L23.H05 (-4.68)\n    35→    - Dual-layer FULL: BREAK passes (40.7%->0.0%, session d=3.07), INDUCE NS (3.3%->2.7%)\n    36→    - FDR updated: 32/39 pass BH (was 30/36)\n    37→  - **Behavioral bridge COMPLETE (pod)**: 600/400 turns, BT+ART 42.3% vs 13.8%, per-token R_V d=-1.64 (p=1.4e-6), AUC=0.655\n    38→  - P0 canonical run Mistral-7B-v0.1 (base) — needs second GPU\n    39→- **P0 Canonical Run (Codex, Instruct model)**:\n    40→  - Hedges' g=-1.47, CI [-1.82, -1.17], p<0.001, n=96/100 selfref, 100 baseline\n    41→  - Artifacts verified: result.json, config.json, provenance.json, per_sample.csv all correct\n    42→  - This is Instruct-v0.2; base v0.1 still needed for paper headline\n    43→- **Key causal numbers (CORRECTED)**:\n    44→  - Necessity: Cohen's h=1.31, OR=33.4 (not d=3.29)\n    45→  - KV behavioral transfer: Cohen's h=0.78, OR=13.96\n    46→  - KV geometry transfer: d=0.11 NS (DISSOCIATION — behavior transfers, geometry doesn't)\n    47→  - Bridge: d=-0.71, n1=80, n2=107, p=9.2e-6\n    48→  - AUROC=0.909, genuine vs deceptive d=-0.06\n    49→- **What CANNOT be claimed**: universal contraction (only 2/5), sufficiency of R_V, V-proj as causal (d=0.22 max), scaling law (R^2=0.047), Pythia-2.8B (data lost), multi-seed robustness, word count prediction\n    50→- **CITATION GUARDRAIL**: \"Noci et al. 2025\" for entropy collapse is HALLUCINATED. Real papers: Noci et al. 2022 NeurIPS (rank collapse), Hong & Lee 2024 (entropy collapse), Dey/Zhang/Noci et al. 2025 (both). Also: Ansuini 2019 = CNNs not transformers; Valeriani 2023 = transformer extension. Key framing: \"Collapse is a bug; Contraction is the Witness\" — existing literature treats collapse as failure mode, our paper frames contraction as computational mode for recursive reasoning. This is the primary white space.\n    51→- **Canonical paths**: `scripts/p0_canonical_pipeline.py` (THE script), `geometric_lens/metrics.py` (THE metric), `prompts/subsets/mistral_hardening_v1.json` (THE prompt contract), `prompts/bank.json` (754 prompts, hash `2ac959a313614329`)\n    52→- **Verification**: `scripts/verify_paper_claims.py` — 100 PASS, 0 FAIL, 2 WARN (as of 2026-03-11 4:08am)\n    53→- **Overnight fixes (2026-03-11 ~4am)**:\n    54→  - Scaling gap CIs corrected in paper Table 1 (Qwen-3B [0.84,2.82], Phi-3 [0.20,1.05], Pythia-6.9B [0.00,0.96])\n    55→  - generate_paper_tables.py now uses bootstrap CIs from raw data instead of normal approximation\n    56→  - verify_paper_claims.py updated to match corrected CIs\n    57→  - STATISTICAL_EVIDENCE_AUDIT.md F4 fixed (d=-3.50 -> h=0.78)\n    58→  - DRAFT_SECTIONS_1_3 d=3.29 -> h=1.31 (all instances)\n    59→  - Paper Table 1 BFs corrected: necessity >10^54, KV >10^18, bridge 6.8x10^3\n    60→  - rv-paper SKILL.md v2.2.0 updated with all corrected values and fixes\n    61→  - `scripts/sync_runpod_results.py` created — processes RunPod results and cross-refs paper claims\n    62→  - **Full paper verification completed**: 100 PASS, 0 FAIL, 2 WARN across 102 claims\n    63→  - Manual verification of remaining claims: C14 (606/1024=sig_entropy), C20 (concept erasure delta_d=0.005), C11 (bridge d=-0.71), C25 (R^2=0.047)\n    64→  - FDR 6 failures verified: Pythia-1B/1.4B/2.8B/6.9B scaling, Pythia-1.4B cross-arch, genuine-vs-deceptive\n    65→  - Head sweep discrepancy noted: 606 = entropy-only count (paper), 681 = either-metric count (not used)\n    66→  - V-proj max |d|=0.22 claim NOT in current paper — only in audit docs; actual path patching V-proj max |d|=0.72\n    67→  - Pythia-2.8B training checkpoints: identical d=1.001 across ALL steps (caching artifact, acknowledged in limitations)\n    68→- **Production code**: `~/mech-interp-latent-lab-phase1/geometric_lens/` (metrics.py, probe.py, hooks.py, models.py)\n    69→"}]},"uuid":"5fa2f3cd-bcf9-4215-9b97-58f0d4b3dabb","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:19:10.610Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"cb710261-b84b-49b3-8661-fdf7a1c3be4c","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
